net.cabezudo.json

Class JSONPair

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.cabezudo.json.JSONElement
      • net.cabezudo.json.JSONPair
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<JSONPair>, JSONable

    public class JSONPair
extends JSONElement
implements java.lang.Comparable<JSONPair>
    A JSON object is build with only one element. A JSON pair. A JSON pair has a key and a value. The key is the property name for an element in a JSON object and the value can be any type of value. A value only can be an object inherited of JSONValue. This class represent the element that contain a JSON object.

    • Method Detail

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(JSONPair jsonPair)
        Compare two JSONPair objects. Two JSONPair are the same if the key is the same and the value is the same. For the comparison the key is compared first. If the key in both objects is the same the value is used to return the result of the comparison. Else, the result is the comparison between keys.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<JSONPair>
        Parameters:
        jsonPair - the JSONPair to be compared.
        Returns:
        the value 0 if the argument string is equal to this string; a value less than 0 if this JSONPair is less than the string argument; and a value greater than 0 if this JSONPair is greater than the JSONPair argument.
